## Common Mistakes & How to Avoid Them

### ❌ Mistake 1: Combining All Phases in One Document
**Wrong**: Creating `METAL_GGUF_MA.md` with everything mixed together  
**Right**: Separate files:
- `docs/math/METAL_GGUF_MATHEMATICS.md` (Phase 2)
- `invariants/INV-XXXX.yaml` (Phase 3a)
- `docs/math/<PROJECT>_LEMMAS_APPENDIX.md` (Phase 3b - add entry)
- `notebooks/math/metal_gguf_validation.ipynb` (Phase 4)

### ❌ Mistake 2: Creating Markdown Instead of Notebook
**Wrong**: `notebooks/metal_gguf_validation.md`  
**Right**: `notebooks/math/metal_gguf_validation.ipynb`

### ❌ Mistake 3: Not Creating Separate Invariant Files
**Wrong**: Listing Inv1, Inv2, Inv3, Inv4 in one document  
**Right**: Create `INV-XXXX.yaml`, `INV-YYYY.yaml`, `INV-ZZZZ.yaml`, `INV-WWWW.yaml` (4 separate files)

### ❌ Mistake 4: Not Adding to Indexes
**Wrong**: Creating invariant but not registering it  
**Right**: Add to `invariants/INDEX.yaml` AND add lemma to `<PROJECT>_LEMMAS_APPENDIX.md` quick index

### ❌ Mistake 5: Wrong File Naming
**Wrong**: `METAL_GGUF_MA.md`, `metal_gguf_validation.md`  
**Right**: `METAL_GGUF_MATHEMATICS.md`, `metal_gguf_validation.ipynb`

